Author: heelanwa
Title: [ANN]MobileBridge Momentum - Revolutionising Marketing & Loyalty. Sale 26.04
Body: Hello Seoul! Momentum in South Korea for Meetup with Supporters! South Korea has an innovative history when it comes to technology. As early adopters, South Korea is well known for its innovation and one of the leading nations when it comes to digital transactions and adoption of new technologies. In 2017, the country was a global leader in the cryptocurrency market, responsible for more trading per capita than any other country in the world. Momentum Protocol is excited to be traveling to Seoul this month with several goals in mind: to create partnerships, strengthen existing ones and to meet potential customers. There will be a meetup for Momentum Supporters at Sungbuk Kumin Hall on Tuesday, 16 April from 10:00- 12:00. In attendance will be Momentum CEO Mr. David Mock and Blockchain and Decentralization Expert Mr. Juergen Hoebarth. They will be giving talks regarding the future of the loyalty rewards ecosystem, brand building, and software solutions. Also speaking will be well-respected Futurist Professor Young-sook Park. If you are in Seoul and would like to be in attendance, please contact Professor Young-sook Park at (tel)02- 313-6300, unfutures@gmail.com .

Author: Boqueron
Title: [ANN]MobileBridge Momentum - Revolutionising Marketing & Loyalty. Sale 26.04
Body: Loyalty Points on the blockchain: an open and fair system.  In traditional Loyalty Programs, your points are stored by the issuer in a 'black box'. And with most of these programs, there's no detailed overview on how many points you've collected, and also no information available on when they are going to expire.  Also, there's no way of telling if 'behind-the-scenes' changes are made to your points, or what's happening to your data.  With Momentum Protocol, this is all going to change. Storing your Loyalty Points on the blockchain will mean that each transaction is open, transparent and can forever be tracked. You will be in charge of your loyalty points, as well as your personal data.  Sound good? Let's go!  Visit www.momentumprotocol.com for more information.

Title: [ANN]MobileBridge Momentum - Revolutionising Marketing & Loyalty. Sale 26.04
Body: Momentum Protocol: The new standard protocol for loyalty programs.  Using blockchain technology, Momentum Protocol will disrupt the world of traditional loyalty programs.  But why use Blockchain?  Well, the unique charateristics of Blockchain technology -including the support for virtual currencies, immutability, transparency and database decentralization- can tackle the issues that many Loyalty Programs are facing today.  The interesting fact is actually that Momentum Protocol is not only using Blockchain technology but is maintaining a hybrid-approach. By combining the Blockchain with non-blockchain technologies we are creating a solution which on one hand is fast and efficient - central to a good customer experience - yet, on the other hand, enjoys the various advantages which blockchain can offer.  Discover Momentum Protocol: www.momentumprotocol.com

Body: Hi there! Thanks for the question and interest! What‚Äôs unique about Momentum is that each of the digital currencies launched on the Momentum platform are backed by ‚Äòbrick and mortar‚Äô companies products and services and therefore carry real-world intrinsic value (unlike 99.9% of digital currencies which are speculative digital currencies) which eliminates volatility both for the brand and for the users. Momentum also features an automated marketing and communication engine, allowing brands to determine the rules for rewarding their customers, suppliers or charitable beneficiaries with digital coins backed by real value. The rules can be set quickly and changed rapidly as the system learns and can be related to purchases, loyalty, attention, insights, customer activity such as coming to a physical shop, attending an event or writing a review or for becoming socially involved or helping others. Customers can enjoy the digital currency with the brands they love, or they can save it, gift it or exchange it into other digital currencies. Since Momentum allows companies to generously reward brand loyalists for becoming involved, creating content, becoming active influencers ‚Äì it will become a source of income for people around the world, creating jobs and bettering the lives of many. Momentum allows brands to efficiently reach people they never would be able to reach before and turn them into loyal customers who get involved, drive brand value, boost business and help improve products.

Gyeongsangbuk-do Province in South Korea is set to make the city Jukes, South Korea‚Äôs Crypto Valley. Body: One of the main questions we continue to receive is the date for our public sale. A fair and important question. The overall crypto and ICO market is still under a lot of pressure, and it would make little sense to complete our ICO whilst the market is in a downturn. We are very fortunate that we are in the position that our soft cap has already been met, so that development can start, and we can await better conditions for our ICO. We will certainly stay 100% committed and energised to make both our private and public sale a massive success! As soon as we have a date, we will of course communicate this as soon as we can.

Author: Triop
Title: [ANN]MobileBridge Momentum - Revolutionising Marketing & Loyalty. Sale 26.04
Body: BLOCKCHAIN NEWSA Flourishing Relationship: Blockchain Technology and Customer Loyalty ‚Äì By: Kees de Vos, CEO of MobileBridge MomentumKees de Vos Published 3 days ago on June 21, 2018 By Kees de Vos  Blockchain is creating significant buzz around the world today. It is rare that anyone, investor or not, will visit a website or publication where it is not referenced in one way or another. When most people that are unfamiliar with the system think of blockchain, they think of it in terms of finance and currency. What many don‚Äôt realize, though, is that blockchain technology is positioning itself to cross over into a wide range of industries. One of the industries with the most promise and potential is the marketing and consumer relations sector. Just as blockchain technology has changed how people transact currencies in a mutually beneficial way, the same can be done in how loyalty is transacted between companies and consumers. Improved relationships increases both monetary and advocacy benefits for companies when done in a way that also provides value and ownership to the customer.

Present reward plans cost 500 Billion USD yearly in the US through the number of unused points is around 100 Billion USD leaving a lot of clients with reward points they neither use nor worth. Platform‚Äôs blockchain tech has the ability to impact strongly on the present state of affairs. The proposed token structure will move unloved prize points into valued goods that can be applied in exchange for assets, utilized for traded and investment.

Author: alexvilis
Title: [ANN]MobileBridge Momentum - Revolutionising Marketing & Loyalty. Sale 26.04
Body: Why loyalty schemes are on their final lap https://medium.com/@keesdevosNL/why-loyalty-schemes-are-on-their-final-lap-d174ad46a911    Most of us have used a loyalty card at some point in our life. Many of us may even have a wallet or purse, bursting at the seams with them. But it would seem that they are on their way, with consumers losing interest and the stores themselves looking for new ways to engage and retain customers. This was highlighted in the UK recently, when supermarket giant Tesco said that it was cutting some of its loyalty card (the Tesco Clubcard) rewards. Some customers did complain, and Tesco backtracked a little, delaying the cut until later in 2018.

Author: hufflepuff4life
Title: [ANN]MobileBridge Momentum - Revolutionising Marketing & Loyalty. Sale 26.04
Body: Dear Momentum community,  Since we started building our community around the Momentum a few weeks ago from nothing, we have made some great progress; we have over 3000 supporters across our Telegram channels (incl China), 1100+ Followers on Twitter and lots of other activity, both online and offline. We are listed on the main listing sites, the reviews and feedback is overwhelmingly positive and our friends and family sale will beat our expectations! However, we want this to be a success for everyone and we believe we are not yet performing at top capacity; Chinese New Year meant we had a delay in our Asian activities and our PR and Marketing haven‚Äôt kicked off properly due to the high demand in the market for the best resources. In brief; it just took us a bit longer to get going!  With that in mind we have decided to delay our public sales by 1 month. What does this mean?  - We will run our friends and family private sales until 23/03, as planned. Early supporters can still join with a min purchase of ‚Ç¨10k and as a gesture to these early supporters, we offer an additional 5% bonus tokens for those that want to buy Momentum tokens before the 23rd! - An extended private sale period will start on 24/03 with revised terms; the minimum purchase will increase to ‚Ç¨50k to allow for a select number of larger token buyers to take part before the public sale. To protect the community and ensure wide distribution of the token after the public sales, we will impose a limit to the private sale and allow a minimum of around ‚Ç¨10M of tokens to be available during the public sale (final no. to be determined).  To ensure people don‚Äôt miss out during the public sale, we will open up our whitelist around the same time.  Over the coming weeks you will notice an increased activity around the Momentum as our marketing efforts really kick in. We will be attending events globally, more and more press will appear and no doubt our social communities will continue to grow. Thank you for your support of the Momentum project, so far, we are looking forward to the exciting weeks ahead of us!

Author: paskal_navi
Title: [ANN]MobileBridge Momentum - Revolutionising Marketing & Loyalty. Sale 26.04
Body: Dear Momentum community,  Since we started building our community around the Momentum a few weeks ago from nothing, we have made some great progress; we have over 3000 supporters across our Telegram channels (incl China), 1100+ Followers on Twitter and lots of other activity, both online and offline. We are listed on the main listing sites, the reviews and feedback is overwhelmingly positive and our friends and family sale will beat our expectations! However, we want this to be a success for everyone and we believe we are not yet performing at top capacity; Chinese New Year meant we had a delay in our Asian activities and our PR and Marketing haven‚Äôt kicked off properly due to the high demand in the market for the best resources. In brief; it just took us a bit longer to get going!  With that in mind we have decided to delay our public sales by 1 month. What does this mean? - We will run our friends and family private sales until 23/03, as planned. Early supporters can still join with a min purchase of ‚Ç¨10k and as a gesture to these early supporters, we offer an additional 5% bonus tokens for those that want to buy Momentum tokens before the 23rd! - An extended private sale period will start on 24/03 with revised terms; the minimum purchase will increase to ‚Ç¨50k to allow for a select number of larger token buyers to take part before the public sale. To protect the community and ensure wide distribution of the token after the public sales, we will impose a limit to the private sale and allow a minimum of around ‚Ç¨10M of tokens to be available during the public sale (final no. to be determined). To ensure people don‚Äôt miss out during the public sale, we will open up our whitelist around the same time.  Over the coming weeks you will notice an increased activity around the Momentum as our marketing efforts really kick in. We will be attending events globally, more and more press will appear and no doubt our social communities will continue to grow. Thank you for your support of the Momentum project, so far, we are looking forward to the exciting weeks ahead of us!  During the public sale, a sliding scale of volume dependant purchase bonuses maybe applied: Week 1 - 5% to 15%bonus dependant on volume and supply Week 2 - 3% to 10%bonus dependant on volume and supply Week 3 - up to 5%bonus dependant on volume and supply Week 4 - No bonus

Title: [ANN]MobileBridge Momentum - Revolutionising Marketing & Loyalty. Sale 26.04
Body: A lot of people do electronic marketing already, but what is clear - globally - that the way people are using loyalty and marketing programs today, simply doesn't work. We are proposing to do something about that and make loyalty programs way more attractive for brands AND consumers!

Author: Kees@MobileBridge
Title: [ANN]MobileBridge Momentum - Revolutionising Marketing & Loyalty. Sale 26.04
Body: Hi! I was a consultant and I was hired by these brands over the years to help them design, implement and roll-out their digital strategies. Whilst working at Salmon, I headed up the technology team that implemented the first 'click & collect' implementation at Argos in the UK. The core of which is still in use to day. At Javelin Group I worked with Walmart.com to advise on their international dot com strategy and worked in Australia with Woolworths. At hybris I worked with the Watsons team in China to establish their global ecommerce infrastructure. These are a few examples, I hope it helps. You can also check my recommendations on my profile, which mention some of the names above. Happy to answer any further questions & thank you for supporting our project!

Author: hufflepuff4life
Title: [ANN]MobileBridge Momentum - Revolutionising Marketing & Loyalty. Sale 26.04
Body: Hi there. The project will be adopted all over the world through partners implimenting the technology for their customers. We expect (retail) partners to create their own token (e.g. Best Burger Token). This token's value will be pegged against the local fiat currency, e.g. 1 token is ‚Ç¨0.01. When a user wants to change their Best Burger Token in bitcoin for example, a conversion rate between BBT and Momentum will be established (most likely the current market rate -/- a margin) and the exchange takes place. This allows the retailers who launch their own coin full control of their eco system. As most of them work in Fiat and none of them want to be exposed to the volatility of a fast moving market.  You can check out biggest MobileBridge customers here (for example Burger King, FAW-Volkswagen) : https://mobilebridge.com/customers/

Body: Hi, the amount of tokens people get for their actions will be determined by every brand or retailer, however, this could be quite a substantial amount. Imagine the scenario where you are a good customer of Adidas, maybe you are a runner. Now Adidas asks you to recommend some of your runner friends to them. This way Adidas gets access to say 5 people that are all possible Adidas customers, right in there target segment; they bare all runners. To find these people normally, through generic advertising will cost them a LOT of of money, now they get direct 1:1 access through an introduction. This is worth quite a bit of money for them!

Author: Kees@MobileBridge
Title: [ANN]MobileBridge Momentum - Revolutionising Marketing & Loyalty. Sale 26.04
Body: Hi Dr. Eck, thank you for your feedback! The Waves Platforms allows people to launch their own coins and is not related to MobileBridge Momentum. It is a separate initiative and the announcement shows the need for companies to have more creative solutions for customer loyalty. The MobileBridge solution that was built for Burger King Russia integrated with its existing loyalty platform. To be clear - the Waves Platform just creates the coin structure, in Momentum, companies will not just be able to create their own loyalty tokens, it will include all the incentive and (loyalty) rewards functionality, and the marketing tooling around it. I hope that answers your questions!

Body: MobileBridge uses the Ethereum blockchain as part of its solution. We are standing on the shoulders of giants, who came up with the ideas (not only came up, but implemented and proved them working for the last years) of the decentralized computer, so it would be unwise not to use what is already available, instead of reinventing the wheel. imagine how much of token economy you could build just using ERC20 tokens. probably its easier to innovate using at this level of abstraction, instead of creating another blockchain.
